-- Portugal Seeks Accelerated EU Drought-Aid Payments, Jornal Says
-- B y   H e n r i q u e   A l m e i d a
-- 2012-03-20T08:18:47Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-20/portugal-seeks-accelerated-eu-drought-aid-payments-jornal-says.html
Portugal  will ask the European
Union today to accelerate the payment of more than 100 million
euros ($132 million) in aid to help alleviate the impact of
drought in farms across the country, Jornal de Negocios said,
citing Secretary of State for Agriculture Jose  Albuquerque .  The  Portuguese government  wants to receive the EU funds
that were due in the second semester between April and July, the
Portuguese newspaper said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Henrique Almeida in Lisbon at 
 halmeida5@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
